Chapters:
0:00 Intro
0:46 The Mountains
6:08 The Coast

The Geography of Taiwan is one of extremes. The geologically young island is dominated by a massive temperate mountain range, which covers the eastern two thirds of Taiwan. This fortes is opposed by the low-lying fertile plains of the west coast, which also accommodates some of the most modern and futuristic cities in the world.

For more geography videos on the most interesting regions of our planet, be sure to subscribe and let me know what topic you would like to see covered next.

Cheers!
